    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-01-12T09:40:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-01-12T09:40:00-05:00" n="222"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d222">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.51/1192.</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Santo Domingo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-01-12T10:00:00-04:40">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 12, 1914, 10 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your January 10, 7 p.m. First inquiry, yes. Second inquiry, yes. Third, Dominican
                    Government agrees and proposes consolidated guaranty asked for that the American
                    Minister shall in the future supervise the daily expenditures of the Dominican
                    Republic that the same may always be kept within budget. Objects to an open
                    comptroller. I believe with this power vested in Department our ability to
                    defeat revolutions and blackmail will be ample and that Dominican Government can
                    be kept solvent. If this seems the solution would earnestly request immediate
                    appointment of commercial attaché to assume the duties which such an arrangement
                    would impose. It seems to me an opportune time to demand increased powers for
                    the Receivership in the collection of customs.</p>
                <p>Please send instructions.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Sullivan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
